i18nStrings.iom_aboutIOM_browser:
Established in 1951, IOM is the leading inter-governmental organization in the field of migration and works closely with governmental, intergovernmental and non-governmental partners.

With 166 member states, a further 8 states holding observer status and offices in over 100 countries, IOM is dedicated to promoting humane and orderly migration for the benefit of all. It does so by providing services and advice to governments and migrants.

IOM works to help ensure the orderly and humane management of migration, to promote international cooperation on migration issues, to assist in the search for practical solutions to migration problems and to provide humanitarian assistance to migrants in need, including refugees and internally displaced people.

The IOM Constitution recognizes the link between migration and economic, social and cultural development, as well as to the right of freedom of movement.

IOM works in the four broad areas of migration management:

  • Migration and development
  • Facilitating migration
  • Regulating migration
  • Forced migration

IOM activities that cut across these areas include the promotion of international migration law, policy debate and guidance, protection of migrants' rights, migration health and the gender dimension of migration.

i18nStrings.i18n_about_vr:
Assisted Voluntary Return and Reintegration (AVRR) is an indispensable part of a comprehensive approach to migration management aiming at orderly and humane return and reintegration of migrants who are unable or unwilling to remain in host countries and wish to return voluntarily to their countries of origin.

The successful implementation of AVRR programmes requires the cooperation and participation of a broad range of actors, including the migrants, civil society and the governments in both host countries and countries of origin. The partnerships created by IOM and a diverse range of national and international stakeholders are essential to the effective implementation of AVRRs - from the pre-return to the reintegration stages.

Beneficiaries


For migrants who need to return home but lack the means to do so, IOMs AVRR programmes are often the only solution to their immediate plight. Beneficiaries of IOMs assistance include:
Individuals whose application for asylum was rejected or withdrawn
Stranded migrants
Victims of trafficking, and
Other vulnerable groups, including unaccompanied migrant children, or those with health-related needs

Vision


As a core activity of IOM, AVRR activities provide vital assistance to thousands of migrants every year. Building on experience and a world-wide network of offices and partners, IOMs AVRR programmes promote international dialogue and cooperation on migration management issues among host and transit countries and countries of origin.

Objectives


IOM strives to support sustainable reintegration of migrants returning to a variety of contexts, recognizing, that the factors affecting the reintegration process and subsequently its sustainability are not dissimilar from those that resulted in the decision to migrate in the first place. IOM therefore asserts that reintegration can be considered sustainable when returnees have reached levels of economic self-sufficiency, social stability within their communities, and psychosocial well-being that allow them to cope with (re)migration drivers. Having achieved sustainable reintegration, returnees are able to make further migration decisions a matter of choice, rather than necessity. To achieve this objective, it is necessary to approach migrant reintegration in a comprehensive manner, considering the factors that can affect reintegration and addressing them in a way to respond to the needs of the individual returnees as well as the communities to which they return in a mutually beneficial way, and address the structural factors at play. Assistance to migrants, communities of return, and structural environments in countries of origin is therefore an essential element to ensuring sustainability of reintegration.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_eligible: If you are eligible for in-kind reintegration assistance, you will receive a letter (Terms of Reference) before departure with the exact amount. With that letter, contact IOM in your country of origin within three months after arrival to start to enrol your desired activity. IOM will guide you through the process and monitor your progress until more or less one year after you have returned

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iom's: IOM's Assisted Voluntary Return & Reintegration (AVRR) programme is currently available in these countries:
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassist:
IOM can assist you in obtaining the right travel documents if you dont have any.

In case you have a medical problem, we can even arrange for you to see a doctor. IOM can also assist you with medication and support before, during and after the journey
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassistdocuments: IOM can assist you in obtaining the right travel documents, if you do not have any, or help you to request your documents from the government. In case you have a medical problem, we can assess your needs together with an independent doctor. IOM can also assist you with medication and support before, during and after the journey. Once everything is ready, and your application is approved, IOM will book your ticket to your final destination.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_netherlands: Since 1991, IOM Netherlands has assisted more than 60,000 people to return to their countries of origin. We are here to make sure you know all your options and we will explain exactly how our service works.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_onceyorapplication:
Once your application is approved, together we can make a plan and you can decide when you would like to travel

IOM staff will make your ticket ready, meet you at the airport and can assist you with check in and custom formalities. Once you land, IOM will meet you upon arrival even arrange transportation from airport to final destination
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_pleaseselect: Please select your country to be included in future AVRR projects.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since:
Since the AVRR program started, we have assisted lots of people who wanted to return home. We are here to make sure you know all your options and we will explain exactly how our service works.

Once you have all the information you need, you can take some time to think about your next step. You can change your mind at any stage of the process and we won't share your information with others.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since1979confidential:
Since 1979, IOM, the UN Migration Agency, has helped over one and a half million people return to their countries of origin, through its assisted voluntary return and reintegration programmes, commonly known as AVRR. We are here to make sure you know all your options and we will explain exactly how our service works

Once you have all the information you need, you can take some time to think about your next step. You can change your mind at any stage of the process and is fully confidential
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since1979won'tshare:
Since 1979, IOM, the UN Migration Agency, has helped over one and a half million people return to their countries of origin, through its assisted voluntary return and reintegration programmes, commonly known as AVRR. We are here to make sure you know all your options and we will explain exactly how our service works

Once you have all the information you need, you can take some time to think about your next step. You can change your mind at any stage of the process and we won't share your information with others
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_understand:
We understand that returning to your country of origin is a big decision.

If you want to return or you want to discuss your options in a confidential manner, IOM can provide assistance tailored to your needs and circumstances.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_upon:
Upon a decision of return, together we can make a plan and you can decide when you would like to travel

IOM staff will have your tickets ready, meet you at the airport and can assist you with check-in and immigration formalities. Once you land, IOM will meet you upon arrival and even arrange transportation from the airport to your final destination.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_weunderstand: We understand returning home can be a difficult decision. If you wish to return or you want to discuss your options in a confidential manner, you can make an appointment for the nearest IOM consultation hour. IOM is present at COA locations and many other locations throughout the country.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_whenyouarrive: When you arrive at the airport, you will go to the IOM Desk where you will receive your ticket. An IOM staff will assist you during the check-in and exit formalities, and, if needed, will also assist you during transit and upon arrival. In case you are eligible for a cash grant, you will receive the amount after check-in.

i18nStrings.i18n_ecointro_iom's:
IOM's Ethics and Conduct Office (ECO) receives, manages and tracks referrals concerning allegations of misconduct and unethical behavior in compliance with the IOM Standards of Conduct and related policy issues, including fraud, harassment, abuse of authority, discrimination and conflicts of interest.

All IOM staff have an obligation to report misconduct and unethical behavior to ECO at eco@iom.int. External parties are also invited to submit any reports or complaints in relation to any breach of IOM Standards of Conduct by an IOM staff directly to ECO: eco@iom.int

i18nStrings.i18n_medical_iomprovides: IOM provides health assessment services in more than 50 clinics around the world, for immigrants going to Australia, Canada, Malaysia, New Zealand, South Korea, United Kingdom and United States. Medical examinations are conducted to protect the health of migrants and of host communities. Receiving countries require these medical examinations as part of the application process for temporary or permanent visas, international employment or enrolment in specific migrant assistance programmes. Proceed to the next step to see a list of IOM clinics, the programmes provided and contact details.

i18nStrings.i18n_termsandconditions:
MigApp User Agreement


Please read the Privacy Policy and General Terms and Conditions governing the MigApp mobile application ("the application"). By clicking "I Agree" below, you are entering into a legally binding agreement with IOM.

Privacy Policy

1. Personal data

When you register with MigApp, you accept to provide some personal information. This includes your email address (or Skype username, Facebook username, etc.), first and last names (or alias), sex, Date of Birth, place of birth and phone number. You may also add a photograph to your profile if you wish.

You certify that all information you provide through MigApp, is true, accurate, and up-to-date. You agree to maintain the security of your account, including by using a secure password and not sharing your password.

2. Additional Information for In-App Features

Your agreement to additional terms may also be requested before accessing certain features of the application.

3. Purpose for Collecting and Processing Your Data

IOM may use your personal data (such as age, sex, country of origin, country of destination) only for the purposes of:

  ●   Contributing to migrants’ safe migration by establishing a communication channel between migrants and IOM and providing migrants with the relevant information specific to their migration experience
  ●   Helping IOM to analyse global, regional or local migration patterns and proactively respond to emerging issues, and
  ●   Improving the application’s usefulness towards achieving these Purposes.This may involve using your personal data to generate statistics and examine trends

IOM will not sell, distribute or rent personal information collected through MigApp.

4. Additional Purposes

IOM may also use and reproduce your location based data for future use in its work, provided that the datais anonymized (used in a manner that no one will be able to connect it to your identity). IOM’s additional purposes may include, but are not limited to:

  ●   Increasing knowledge and understanding of migration issues
  ●   Raising awareness in campaigns, promotional activities, communication strategies and public communications
  ●   Documenting and promoting IOM’s work
  ●   Informing IOM’s donors, partners, the media, the general public and others about IOM’s programmes and activities

In order to achieve these additional purposes,IOM may use or reproduce your data (always anonymized) in publications, promotional material, brochures, reports, articles, presentations, future exhibitions and display on the websites of IOM and other third-party electronic format media outlets.

5. Security of Your Data

IOM commits to make its best efforts to maintain the security and confidentiality of your personal information, including through encryption and other methods. As an international organization, IOM enjoys privileges and immunities that help protect your data from being accessed by governments and other third parties.

6. Confidentiality of Personal Data

Any personal data collected, received, used, transferred, or stored by IOM are protected by strict conditions of confidentiality and security, as detailed in the IOM Data Protection Principles. Aside from the limited situation described in point 7 below, IOM will not disclose your information to any third party without your prior informed consent. Access to your personal data will be limited only to IOM staff members on specific teams dedicated to managing MigApp. These staff members are strictly bound by confidentiality obligations.

7. Sharing Data to Prevent Harm, Report on Missing Migrants or Comply with International Law

IOM may preserve your information and share it with third parties if the Organization has a good faith belief that doing so is necessary to prevent death or immediate bodily harm to you or others, help locate migrants who have been reported missing, or prevent violations of international law.

8. Right to Change and Delete Your Data

You have the right to update all personal data you have supplied to MigApp, always remembering that the information you provide on MigApp must be true, accurate and up-to-date.

  ●   You may change your personal data in your account settings
  ●   If you choose to delete your MigApp account, all personal data will be deleted from IOM’s files and IOM will only keep aggregated data for statistical purposes

If your profile is inactive for two years, IOM will assume that you are no longer interested in the MigApp services and will delete your personal data from its files, only keeping aggregated data (always anonymized) for statistical purposes.

9. Requesting Personal Data

At any time, you may request a copy of all your personal data that has been gathered through MigApp regarding your account, which will then be sent to you via email. If you have not provided an email address with your registration, IOM will request one to send you your information. Please direct all requests for MigApp personal data to:
E-mail: migapp@iom.int.

10. Notification of Changes

IOM reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time. Whenever changes are made, you will be notified and will need to agree in order to continue using the application.


General Terms and Conditions

1. Use of MigApp

You agree to the following obligations:

  ●   Not to use MigApp if you are under the age of 16
  ●   Not to misrepresent your relationship to another user
  ●   Not to use MigApp to act in an unlawful, obscene, discriminatory or abusive manner or promote such actions
  ●   Not to sell, rent, trade or otherwise monetize any feature of MigApp or any information accessed through the application
  ●   Not to collect, use, copy, or transfer any information obtained from MigApp without the consent of IOM
  ●   Not to use MigApp to violate the intellectual property rights of other persons or entities
  ●   Not to use bots, scripts or any other automated method to access and collect information on MigApp
  ●   Not to override any security feature of the application

2. Denying Access

IOM reserves the right to deny, at its sole discretion, any user access to the application or any portion thereof without notice.

3. Disclaimer

The content in MigApp is provided on an "as is" basis, without warranty of any kind. IOM specifically does not make any warranties as to the appropriateness, quality, timeliness, accuracy or completeness of the information and services offered through MigApp. While IOM cannot guarantee that there are no errors in the information provided, it does endeavour to correct errors that are drawn to its attention.

4. Boundaries and Geographic Names

The boundaries, geographic names and related data shown in MigApp are not warranted to be error free nor imply judgement on the legal status of any territory, or any endorsement or acceptance of such boundaries by IOM.

5. Content from third parties and service providers

IOM does not represent or endorse the accuracy or reliability of any advice, opinion, statement or other information provided by any content providers, third parties in the application, any user of the app or any other person or entity. Reliance upon any such opinion, advice, statement, or other information shall be at your own risk.

While IOM has a strong interest in the integrity of its online service providers, it does not provide any warranties and specifically disclaims any liability in connection with the services. IOM further disclaims any liability of any nature for any loss or damage caused in connection with using any of the services.

6. Other Applications and Websites

IOM does not necessarily support policies and beliefs of organizations and individuals listed or referred to in materials held on the services, applications and websites referred to in MigApp.

IOM does not provide any warranties and specifically disclaims any liability in connection with third party applications or websites. The inclusion of a link or reference in MigApp does not imply the endorsement of the linked application or site by IOM.

7. Other Users

You acknowledge and agree that IOM is not liable for any conduct of any user.

8. Bugs, Virus, Malicious Code, etc.

While IOM makes every effort to ensure the materials available on the application are free of any software virus, it cannot guarantee that they are free from any or all software viruses. IOM is not responsible for any loss or damage caused by software and related codes, including viruses and worms.

9. Security Measures

MigApp implements a series of technologies and security measures in order to safeguard the information maintained by IOM from misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure, alteration or loss.

Although IOM applies reasonable means to ensure that the information you provide is not used by third parties for purposes other than that for which you accepted to provide it, IOM cannot guarantee that unauthorized third parties will never be able to defeat security measures or use your personal data for improper purposes. You should be aware that no transmission of information via the internet is ever totally secure. Transmission of personal data is at your own risk.

10. Messages addressed to IOM

IOM attempts to respond to messages directed at the organization sent through MigApp. However, IOM is under no obligation to respond to any or all such messages.

11. Intellectual Property

All intellectual property rights relating to IOM-owned materials provided through MigApp shall remain vested in IOM, unless otherwise stated. All materials provided through MigApp are copyright of the IOM, unless otherwise stated. The materials may be viewed, downloaded, and printed for personal, non-commercial use only, without any right to sell, resell, or create derivative works therefrom.

Permission to use materials which are not owned by IOM must be requested from the copyright owner.

12. Information on the Migration Experience

The Migration Services information provided by IOM in MigApp is updated regularly may be shared freely without the right to sell or charge for its use, provided IOM is specifically and clearly identified as the source of the materials.

Mention of IOM as the source of the materials shall not be made in any way that would implicitly or explicitly assert or suggest endorsement, sponsorship of or affiliation by IOM.

13. Contact

If you have any questions or concerns about this User Agreement please contact:
E-mail: ocu@iom.int

14. Notification of Changes

IOM reserves the right to change the General Terms and Conditions at any time, without notice. IOM will post changes to the General Terms and Conditions in this application.

15. Privileges and Immunities

Nothing in or relating to these General Terms and Conditions shall be deemed a waiver, express or implied, of any of the privileges and immunities of the IOM as an intergovernmental organization.

16. Termination

The IOM reserves the exclusive right and discretion to limit, alter, suspend or terminate the Application without notice, in whole or in part, at any time without giving any reason or explanation and without incurring any liability to the user for doing so.

I am a migrant

"I am a migrant" is designed to help you share your migration story in the I am a migrant platform. The information that you post in this section, including messages, photos and videos, will be visible to the public via the website for the purpose of participating in the I am a migrant project. This is a platform where personal stories of migrants are shared on the I am a migrant website, on social media and other equivalent means, aiming to challenge the anti-migrant stereotypes and hate speech in politics and society. The information shared with authorized IOM staff and other registered users includes the metadata associated with your posts, such as the location, time and date.

In addition to the MigApp Terms and Conditions and the MigApp Privacy Policy, by clicking on "I Agree" below, you also accept the following:

1. Purpose

You have read and understand the purposes for which your personal data (name or alias, country of origin, country of destination, photograph) and the information of your migration experience ("the content") will be collected, processed and shared in I am a migrant as described above.

2. Consent

You have read this and authorize IOM to collect, process and share your personal data and content, including messages, photos and videos.

3. Sharing data

You authorize IOM to share your personal data and content in the I am a migrant website and any other platform of the I am a migrant initiative, such as Twitter, Facebook, Instagram and others.

4. Correct information

You declare that the information you provide in the content is true and correct to the best of your knowledge.

5. Content edit

You may change or remove your content in I am a migrant at any time by using the website.

6. Appropriate use

You will not use the I am a migrant to act in an unlawful, obscene, discriminatory or abusive manner or to promote such actions.

7. Intellectual property

In using I am a migrant, you will not violate the intellectual property rights of other persons or entities.

IOM reserves the right to remove your content if it considers that it may constitute an offense to other users or a violation of intellectual property rights of others.

Secure my documents

Disclaimer: By using Secure my documents you accept that IOM is not responsible for your loss of the password giving access to your documents and understand that the documents you upload are encrypted and accessible only by you.

*****

Secure my documents has been designed to allow you to upload to the application copies of the personal documents that you may need during your migration experience, such as passport, national identification documents or certificates. IOM will collect and store your documents without accessing, processing or using them, for the purpose of giving you the possibility of storing electronic copies of the documents that you may need in your migration experience.

In addition to the MigApp Terms and Conditions and the MigApp Privacy Policy, by using Secure my documents, you also accept the following:

1. Purpose, consent and correct use of service

You understand the Purpose of this service and voluntarily and freely accept to upload your personal documents to the application. You accept to only upload copies of documents that may be relevant to your migration process and not personal, private documents or photographs. Kindly note that there is a limited space of 6MB per MigApp user in the Secure my documents function.

2. Security measures

You understand that, though IOM makes its best efforts to maintain the security and confidentiality of your personal information, it cannot guarantee that unauthorized third parties will never be able to defeat the security measures or use your personal information for improper purposes.

3. Use of data

You understand that IOM will not use or process the information contained in your documents. IOM will store your documents in the application without making use of them.

4. Disclaimer

You understand the risks of transmission and storage of information via the internet and accept that the use of Secure my documents is at your own risk. You release, discharge and agree to hold harmless IOM, its officers, employees and agents from any liability or damage caused, directly or indirectly, to you, your family or relatives in connection with this authorization by virtue of the use or disclosure of your personal data for the Purposes described above.

Share my location

Disclaimer: By using Share my location you accept the responsibility for choosing carefully the recipient of this information and understand that IOM will only use your location to transmit it to the person of your choice.

*****

"Share my location" is a tool that allows you to share your position. Through this service, IOM collects your location with the purpose of obtaining your GPS coordinates and process them in order to send them to a person of your choice, via SMS or email [insert other methods as applicable], to help your loved ones keep track of your journey.

In addition to the MigApp Terms and Conditions and the MigApp Privacy Policy, by using Share my location you also accept the following:

1. Purpose and consent for collection

You have been informed about and understand the purpose for which your location will be collected, processed and transmitted as described above and you voluntarily and freely consent to sharing your location data through MigApp.

2. Correct information

You declare that the information you provide through "Share my location" is true and correct to the best of your knowledge.

3. Security measures

You understand that, though IOM makes its best efforts to maintain the security and confidentiality of your personal data, it cannot guarantee that unauthorized third parties will never be able to defeat the security measures or use your personal information for improper purposes.

4. Use of data

You understand that IOM will not use or process the information sent in this communication for any purpose other than the one described above. IOM will not retain your location information and will not share it with third parties beyond your request to share your location.

5. Disclaimer

You understand the risks of transmission of information via the internet and accept that the use of Share my location is at your own risk. You release, discharge and agree to hold harmless IOM, its officers, employees and agents from any liability or damage caused, directly or indirectly, to you, your family or relatives in connection with this authorization by virtue of the use or disclosure of your personal data for the Purposes described above.

You have the right to update all personal data you have supplied to MigApp, always remembering that the information you provide on MigApp must be true, accurate and up-to-date.

You may change your personal data in your account settings
If you choose to delete your MigApp account, all personal data will be deleted from IOMs files and IOM will only keep aggregated data for statistical purposes

If your profile is inactive for two years, IOM will assume that you are no longer interested in the MigApp services and will delete your personal data from its files, only keeping aggregated data (always anonymized) for statistical purposes.

9. Requesting Personal Data

At any time, you may request a copy of all your personal data that has been gathered through MigApp regarding your account, which will then be sent to you via email. If you have not provided an email address with your registration, IOM will request one to send you your information. Please direct all requests for MigApp personal data to:
E-mail: migapp@iom.int.

10. Notification of Changes

IOM reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time. Whenever changes are made, you will be notified and will need to agree in order to continue using the application.

"I am a migrant" is designed to help you share your migration story in the I am a migrant platform. The information that you post in this section, including messages, photos and videos, will be visible to the public via the website for the purpose of participating in the I am a migrant project. This is a platform where personal stories of migrants are shared on the I am a migrant website, on social media and other equivalent means, aiming to challenge the anti-migrant stereotypes and hate speech in politics and society. The information shared with authorized IOM staff and other registered users includes the metadata associated with your posts, such as the location, time and date.

In addition to the MigApp Terms and Conditions and the MigApp Privacy Policy, by clicking on "I Agree" below, you also accept the following:

1. Purpose

You have read and understand the purposes for which your personal data (name or alias, country of origin, country of destination, photograph) and the information of your migration experience ("the content") will be collected, processed and shared in I am a migrant as described above.

2. Consent

You have read this and authorize IOM to collect, process and share your personal data and content, including messages, photos and videos.

3. Sharing data

You authorize IOM to share your personal data and content in the I am a migrant website and any other platform of the I am a migrant initiative, such as Twitter, Facebook, Instagram and others.

4. Correct information

You declare that the information you provide in the content is true and correct to the best of your knowledge.

5. Content edit

You may change or remove your content in I am a migrant at any time by using the website.

6. Appropriate use

You will not use the I am a migrant to act in an unlawful, obscene, discriminatory or abusive manner or to promote such actions.

7. Intellectual property

In using I am a migrant, you will not violate the intellectual property rights of other persons or entities.

IOM reserves the right to remove your content if it considers that it may constitute an offense to other users or a violation of intellectual property rights of others.

i18nStrings.iom_aboutIOM_browser:
Established in 1951, IOM is the leading inter-governmental organization in the field of migration and works closely with governmental, intergovernmental and non-governmental partners.

With 166 member states, a further 8 states holding observer status and offices in over 100 countries, IOM is dedicated to promoting humane and orderly migration for the benefit of all. It does so by providing services and advice to governments and migrants.

IOM works to help ensure the orderly and humane management of migration, to promote international cooperation on migration issues, to assist in the search for practical solutions to migration problems and to provide humanitarian assistance to migrants in need, including refugees and internally displaced people.

The IOM Constitution recognizes the link between migration and economic, social and cultural development, as well as to the right of freedom of movement.

IOM works in the four broad areas of migration management:

  • Migration and development
  • Facilitating migration
  • Regulating migration
  • Forced migration

IOM activities that cut across these areas include the promotion of international migration law, policy debate and guidance, protection of migrants' rights, migration health and the gender dimension of migration.

i18nStrings.iom_about_Introduction_faqA1: IOM has developed the Migrant App (MigApp), an application which can be downloaded into any mobile device and which can be downloaded into any mobile device and which offers migrants and migrants-to-be a user-friendly, one-stop-shop platform from where they can directly access IOM services in a secure environment or access readily available migration information and services relevant to their specific migration process. MigApp is a response to the increased usage of mobile phones before, during and after migration. MigApp allows IOM to reach a broader range of migrants.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA1: Through the registration process, MigApp will capture the personal information, such as age, gender, country of origin and country of destination. Some features will be available without registration (no data will be collected).
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA10: Yes, for certain features: Remittances, Information, Notifications, Dr. Translate, IOM News, Q&A, Invite Users. For other features,  MigApp users will be requested basic personal information in order to use the services.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA11: Yes, you can update any of the following information at any time: photo, country location, telephone and email address through your profile.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA12: No, IOM does not monitor the location of MigApp users. If location-based data is used by IOM for its work, the data will be anonymized so that no one will be able to connect it to the identity of the migrant.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA13: MigApp cannot be used as a form of official or formal identification.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA2: Data collected through MigApp will be encrypted. It will belong to IOM and will be used to analyse global, regional, or local migration patterns. The results of such analyses may feed into future migration-related programming, research/studies, that will help IOM to proactively respond to emerging issues. Any collection, use, disclosure or disposal of personal data will be done according to the IOM Data Protection Principles.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA3: Only IOM staff members from specific relevant programmes (on a need-to-know basis).
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA4: Your data will be stored in a certified cloud. All data and communication will be encrypted.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA5: Communication and exchange of data between the migrant's mobile device and the MigApp platform will be encrypted thus safeguarding migrant information.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA6: It will be recorded in an encrypted format. Destruction of recorded data will be guided by IOMs data retention period. The IOM data Protection Principles will provide guidance.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA9: They download the app on the new phone and log in with their registered user ID and password. Since there is no personal information stored on the phone, the user can just download the app into his/her new phone, log in with his/her credentials and access his/her data, which will still be there. Please remember that no transmission and storage of information via the internet is ever totally secure. Therefore, upload of personal information and documents is at your own risk and we strongly encourage you to use passwords and/or screen locks in your phone.

i18nStrings.i18n_about_vr:
El retorno y voluntario asistido y la reintegracin son una parte indispensable de un enfoque integral de la gestin migratoria que tiene por objeto el retorno y la reintegracin ordenados y humanos de los migrantes que no pueden o no quieren permanecer en los pases de acogida o de trnsito y desean regresar voluntariamente a sus pases de origen.

La implementacin satisfactoria de los programas de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin requiere la cooperacin y la participacin de un amplio abanico de interlocutores, incluidos los migrantes, la sociedad civil y los gobiernos tanto de los pases de acogida, de trnsito y de origen. Las asociaciones creadas por la OIM y distintos interlocutores nacionales e internacionales son esenciales para la aplicacin efectiva de los programas de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin desde la preparacin del retorno hasta la etapa de reintegracin.


Beneficiarios


Para los migrantes que necesitan regresar a sus hogares pero carecen de medios para hacerlo, los programas de retorno y voluntario asistido y reintegracin de la OIM son a menudo la nica solucin a su difcil situacin. Los beneficiarios de la asistencia de la OIM comprenden:
● personas cuya solicitud de asilo ha sido rechazada o retirada
● migrantes desamparados
● vctimas de la trata, y
● otros grupos vulnerables, incluidos los nios migrantes no acompaados o los que tienen necesidades relacionadas con la salud.

Perspectiva


Como iniciativa fundamental de la OIM, las actividades de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin proporcionan asistencia vital a miles de migrantes cada ao. Basndose en su experiencia y en una red mundial de oficinas y asociados, los programas de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin de la OIM promueven el dilogo y la cooperacin internacionales sobre cuestiones relativas a la gestin de la migracin entre los pases de acogida y de trnsito y los pases de origen.

Objetivos


La OIM se esfuerza por apoyar la reintegracin sostenible de los migrantes que regresan a distintos contextos, reconociendo que los factores que afectan al proceso de reintegracin y, posteriormente, a su sostenibilidad no difieren de los que propiciaron la decisin de migrar en primer lugar. Por lo tanto, la OIM afirma que la reintegracin puede considerarse sostenible cuando quienes retornan han alcanzado niveles de autosuficiencia econmica, estabilidad social en sus comunidades y bienestar psicosocial que les permiten hacer frente a los factores que impulsan una nueva migracin. Una vez lograda la reintegracin sostenible, los migrantes que han retornado pueden tomar nuevas decisiones migratorias basadas en su eleccin y no en la necesidad. Para lograr este objetivo, es necesario abordar la reintegracin de los migrantes de manera integral, considerando los factores que pueden afectar a la reintegracin y dndoles respuesta de manera que satisfagan las necesidades individuales de cada uno, as como de las comunidades a las que retornan, de manera mutuamente beneficiosa, y abordar asimismo los factores estructurales en juego. Por lo tanto, la asistencia a los migrantes, las comunidades de retorno y los entornos estructurales en los pases de origen es un elemento esencial para garantizar la sostenibilidad de la reintegracin.

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_about: Acerca del Retorno voluntario asistido y la reintegracin
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_eligible: Si cumple los requisitos para beneficiarse de asistencia de reintegracin en especie, recibir una carta (Mandato) antes de su partida con el importe exacto. Con esa carta, pngase en contacto con la OIM en su pas de origen en los tres meses siguientes a su llegada para comenzar su inscripcin en la actividad deseada. La OIM le guiar a travs del proceso y supervisar su progreso hasta aproximadamente un ao despus de su regreso.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_establishedin1951:
La OIM fue creada en 1951 y es la principal organizacin intergubernamental en el mbito de la migracin. Trabaja estrechamente con asociados gubernamentales, intergubernamentales y no gubernamentales.

Con 166 Estados Miembros, 8 Estados que gozan del estatuto de observador y oficinas en ms de 100 pases, la OIM est consagrada a promover una migracin ordenada y en condiciones humanas en beneficio de los migrantes y de la sociedad. Para ello presta servicios y asesoramiento a gobiernos y migrantes.

La OIM trabaja para ayudar a garantizar la gestin ordenada y humana de la migracin, promover la cooperacin internacional sobre cuestiones migratorias, apoyar la bsqueda de soluciones prcticas a los problemas migratorios y prestar asistencia humanitaria a los migrantes necesitados, incluidos los refugiados y los desplazados internos.

La Constitucin de la OIM reconoce el nexo entre la migracin y el desarrollo econmico, social y cultural, as como el derecho a la libertad de circulacin

La OIM trabaja en estas cuatro esferas de gestin de la migracin:

  • Migracin y desarrollo
  • Migracin facilitada
  • Migracin regulada

Las actividades de la OIM que abarcan estas esferas comprenden la promocin del derecho internacional sobre migracin, la orientacin y el debate normativo, la proteccin de los derechos de los migrantes, la salud migratoria y la dimensin de gnero de la migracin.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iom's: El Programa de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin de la OIM est actualmente disponible en estos pases:
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassist:
La OIM puede ayudarle a obtener los documentos de viaje adecuados si no dispone de ellos.

En caso de que tenga un problema de salud, podemos incluso concertar una cita con un mdico. La OIM tambin puede ayudarle con medicamentos y apoyo antes, durante y despus del viaje.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassistdocuments: La OIM puede ayudarle a obtener los documentos de viaje adecuados, si no dispone de los mismos, o a solicitarlos al Gobierno. En caso de que tenga un problema mdico, podemos evaluar sus necesidades junto a un mdico independiente. La OIM tambin puede prestarle asistencia con medicamentos y apoyo antes, durante y despus del viaje. Una vez que todo est listo y su solicitud haya sido aprobada, la OIM reservar el billete hasta su destino final.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_netherlands: Desde 1991, la Oficina de la OIM en los Pases Bajos ha prestado asistencia a ms de 60.000 personas para que regresen a sus pases de origen. Nuestro objetivo es asegurarnos de que conoce todas sus opciones y explicarle cmo funciona exactamente nuestro servicio.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_onceyorapplication:
Una vez que su solicitud sea aprobada, podemos trazar un plan conjuntamente y puede decidir cundo le gustara viajar.

El personal de la OIM preparar su billete, le recibir en el aeropuerto y le ayudar con los trmites de facturacin y aduanas. Una vez que aterrice, la OIM se reunir con usted, incluso organizar el transporte desde el aeropuerto hasta el destino final.

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since:
Since the AVRR program started, we have assisted lots of people who wanted to return home. We are here to make sure you know all your options and we will explain exactly how our service works.

Once you have all the information you need, you can take some time to think about your next step. You can change your mind at any stage of the process and we won't share your information with others.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since1979confidential:
Desde 1979, la OIM, el Organismo de las Naciones Unidas para la Migracin, ha ayudado a ms de un milln y medio de personas a regresar a sus pases de origen, a travs de sus programas de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin, comnmente conocidos como programas AVRR. Nuestro objetivo es asegurarnos de que conoce todas sus opciones y explicarle cmo funciona exactamente nuestro servicio.

Una vez que tenga toda la informacin que necesita, puede tomarse un tiempo para reflexionar sobre su prximo paso. Puede cambiar de opinin en cualquier etapa del proceso y ello seguir siendo plenamente confidencial.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since1979won'tshare:
Desde 1979, la OIM, el Organismo de las Naciones Unidas para la Migracin, ha ayudado a ms de un milln y medio de personas a regresar a sus pases de origen, a travs de sus programas de retorno voluntario asistido y reintegracin, comnmente conocidos como programas AVRR. Nuestro objetivo es asegurarnos de que conoce todas sus opciones y explicarle cmo funciona exactamente nuestro servicio.

Una vez que tenga toda la informacin que necesita, puede tomarse un tiempo para reflexionar sobre su prximo paso. Puede cambiar de opinin en cualquier etapa del proceso y no compartiremos su informacin con otras personas.

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_understand:
Entendemos que regresar a su pas de origen es una decisin importante.

Si desea regresar o hablar de sus opciones de manera confidencial, la OIM puede prestarle asistencia adaptada a sus necesidades y circunstancias.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_upon:
Si decide retornar, podemos trazar un plan conjuntamente y puede decidir asimismo cundo le gustara viajar.

El personal de la OIM preparar su billete, le recibir en el aeropuerto y le ayudar con los trmites de facturacin e inmigracin. Una vez que aterrice, la OIM se reunir con usted, e incluso organizar el transporte desde el aeropuerto hasta el destino final.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_weunderstand: Entendemos que volver a casa puede ser una decisin difcil. Si desea retornar o analizar sus opciones de manera confidencial, puede concertar una cita para la prxima hora de consulta disponible en la OIM. La OIM est presente en las oficinas del Organismo Central de Acogida Solicitantes de Asilo y en muchos otros lugares del pas.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_whenyouarrive: Al llegar al aeropuerto, se dirigir al mostrador de la OIM donde se le entregar su billete. Un miembro del personal de la OIM le prestar asistencia durante los trmites de facturacin y salida y, si es necesario, tambin le ayudar durante el trnsito y a su llegada. En caso de que cumpla las condiciones para recibir un subsidio en efectivo, recibir el importe despus de la facturacin.

La OIM trabaja para ayudar a garantizar la gestin ordenada y humana de la migracin, promover la cooperacin internacional en cuestiones migratorias, prestar asistencia en la bsqueda de soluciones prcticas a los problemas migratorios y prestar asistencia humanitaria a los migrantes que la necesitan, incluidos los refugiados y los desplazados internos.

La Constitucin de la OIM reconoce el nexo entre la migracin y el desarrollo econmico, social y cultural, as como el derecho a la libertad de circulacin.

La OIM trabaja en las cuatro esferas amplias de la gestin de la migracin:

Migracin y desarrollo
Migracin facilitada
Migracin regulada
Migracin forzosa

Las actividades de la OIM que abarcan estos mbitos incluyen la promocin del derecho internacional sobre migracin, el debate y la orientacin normativos, la proteccin de los derechos de los migrantes, la migracin y la salud, y los aspectos de gnero en la migracin.

i18nStrings.i18n_termsandconditions:
Acuerdo de usuario de MigApp


Lea la Poltica de privacidad y los Trminos y condiciones generales que rigen la aplicacin mvil MigApp ("la aplicacin"). Al hacer clic en "Acepto" a continuacin, est celebrando un acuerdo legalmente vinculante con la OIM

Poltica de privacidad

1. Datos personales

Cuando se registra con MigApp, acepta proporcionar los siguientes datos personales: direccin de correo electrnico (o nombre de usuario de Skype, nombre de usuario de Facebook, etc.), nombre y apellido (o alias), sexo, fecha de nacimiento, lugar de nacimiento. Tambin puede agregar su nmero de telfono y una foto si lo desea.

Usted certifica que toda la informacin que proporciona a travs de MigApp es verdadera, precisa y actualizada. Acepta mantener la seguridad de su cuenta, lo que incluye el uso de una contrasea segura y no compartir su contrasea.

2. Informacin adicional para las caractersticas en la aplicacin

Tambin puede solicitar su aceptacin de trminos adicionales antes de acceder a ciertas caractersticas de la aplicacin

3. Propsito para recopilar y procesar sus datos personales

La OIM puede utilizar sus datos personales (como edad, sexo, pas de origen, pas de destino) solo a los efectos de ("Propsitos"):

  ●  Proporcionndole la informacin relevante especfica para su experiencia de migracin
  ●  Analizar los patrones de migracin globales, regionales o locales y responder proactivamente a los problemas emergentes, aumentando el conocimiento y la comprensin de los problemas de migracin. Esto puede implicar la agregacin de datos personales para generar estadsticas y examinar tendencias; y
  ●   Mejorar la utilidad de la aplicacin para lograr estos Propsitos.

i18nStrings.iom_aboutIOM_browser:
La OIM fue creada en 1951 y es la principal organizacin intergubernamental en el mbito de la migracin. Trabaja estrechamente con asociados gubernamentales, intergubernamentales y no gubernamentales.

With 166 member states, a further 8 states holding observer status and offices in over 100 countries, IOM is dedicated to promoting humane and orderly migration for the benefit of all. It does so by providing services and advice to governments and migrants.

La OIM trabaja para ayudar a garantizar la gestin ordenada y humana de la migracin, promover la cooperacin internacional sobre cuestiones migratorias, apoyar la bsqueda de soluciones prcticas a los problemas migratorios y prestar asistencia humanitaria a los migrantes necesitados, incluidos los refugiados y los desplazados internos.

La Constitucin de la OIM reconoce el nexo entre la migracin y el desarrollo econmico, social y cultural, as como el derecho a la libertad de circulacin.

La OIM trabaja en estas cuatro esferas de gestin de la migracin:

  • Migracin y desarrollo
  • Migracin facilitada
  • Migracin regulada
  • Migracin forzosa

Las actividades de la OIM que abarcan estas esferas comprenden la promocin del derecho internacional sobre migracin, la orientacin y el debate normativo, la proteccin de los derechos de los migrantes, la salud migratoria y la dimensin de gnero de la migracin.

i18nStrings.iom_about_Introduction_faqA1: La OIM ha desarrollado la MigApp, una aplicacin para migrantes que se puede descargar en cualquier dispositivo mvil y que ofrece a los migrantes y futuros migrantes una plataforma de ventanilla nica y fcil de usar desde la que pueden acceder directamente a los servicios de la OIM en un entorno seguro, o acceder a informacin y servicios de migracin de fcil disponibilidad y pertinentes para su proceso de migracin especfico. La MigApp es una iniciativa de respuesta al aumento del uso del telfono mvil antes, durante y despus de la migracin. La MigApp permite a la OIM asistir a un abanico ms amplio de migrantes.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA1: Mediante el proceso de registro, la MigApp recopilar datos personales, tales como la edad, el sexo, el pas de origen y el pas de destino. Algunas funciones estarn disponibles sin registro (no se recopilarn datos).
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA10: S, para ciertas funciones: Remesas, Informacin, Notificaciones, Traductor mdico, Noticias de la OIM, Preguntas frecuentes, Invitar a Usuarios. Para otras funciones, se solicitar informacin personal bsica a los usuarios de la MigApp a fin de que puedan utilizar los servicios.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA11: S, puede actualizar cualquiera de los siguientes datos en cualquier momento: fotografa, pas de ubicacin, telfono y direccin de correo electrnico a travs de su perfil.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA12: No, la OIM no controla la ubicacin de los usuarios de la MigApp. En caso de que la OIM utilice datos basados en la localizacin para su trabajo, se dotar de carcter annimo a los datos para que nadie pueda vincularlos a la identidad del migrante.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA13: La MigApp no se puede utilizar como un medio de identificacin oficial o formal.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA2: Los datos recopilados a travs de la MigApp se cifrarn; pertenecern a la OIM y se utilizarn para analizar los patrones migratorios mundiales, regionales o locales. Los resultados de esos anlisis pueden contribuir a futuros programas, investigaciones y estudios relacionados con la migracin, que ayudarn a la OIM a responder de manera proactiva a las cuestiones emergentes. Toda recopilacin, uso, divulgacin o eliminacin de datos personales se har de acuerdo con los Principios de proteccin de datos de la OIM.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA3: Solo los miembros de personal de la OIM de programas especficos pertinentes (sobre la base de una necesidad de conocer dichos datos).
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA4: Sus datos se almacenarn en una nube certificada. Todos los datos y comunicaciones sern cifrados.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA5: La comunicacin y el intercambio de datos entre el dispositivo mvil del migrante y la plataforma MigApp estar cifrada para proteger la informacin de los migrantes.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA6: Se registrarn en un formato cifrado. La eliminacin de los datos registrados se regir por el perodo de conservacin de datos estipulado por la OIM. Ello cumplir asimismo con los Principios de Proteccin de Datos de la OIM.
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA8: Principios de Proteccin de Datos de la OIM http://publications.iom.int/system/files/pdf/iomdataprotection_web.pdf
i18nStrings.iom_about_Security_faqA9: El usuario deber descargar la aplicacin en el nuevo telfono e iniciar sesin con su nombre de usuario y contrasea registrados. Dado que no hay informacin personal almacenada en el telfono, el usuario solo tendr que descargar la aplicacin en su nuevo telfono, iniciar sesin con sus credenciales y acceder a sus datos, que seguirn estando all.Cabe recordar que ninguna transferencia o almacenamiento de informacin a travs de Internet es totalmente segura. Por lo tanto, el almacenamiento de informacin y documentos personales se realizar bajo su cuenta y riesgo. Por ello, le recomendamos encarecidamente que utilice contraseas y/o bloqueos de pantalla en su telfono.

i18nStrings.i18n_about_vr:
Laide au retour volontaire et la rintgration (AVRR) est un volet incontournable dune approche globale de gestion des migrations visant favoriser, de manire humaine et ordonne, le retour et la rintgration des migrants qui ne peuvent ou ne veulent pas rester dans le pays daccueil ou de transit et prfrent rentrer dans leur pays dorigine.

La bonne mise en uvre des programmes daide au retour volontaire et la rintgration (AVRR) requiert la coopration et la participation dun large ventail dacteurs, dont les migrants, la socit civile et les gouvernements des pays daccueil, de transit et dorigine. Les partenariats nous par lOIM et les diverses parties prenantes nationales et internationales contribuent de manire dterminante la bonne mise en uvre de lAVRR, de la phase prcdant le retour celle de la rintgration.


Bnficiaires


Pour les migrants qui doivent rentrer au pays mais qui nen ont pas les moyens, les programmes AVRR de lOIM sont souvent lunique remde leur situation. Les services dassistance de lOIM sadressent aux catgories de personnes suivantes:
● les individus dont la demande dasile a t rejete ou retire
● les migrants en dtresse
● les victimes de traite; et
● les autres groupes vulnrables, notamment les enfants migrants non accompagns ou ceux ayant besoin dune aide mdicale.

Vision:


En tant quactivit essentielle de lOIM, les programmes AVRR offrent une aide vitale des milliers de migrants chaque anne. Sappuyant sur lexprience et sur un rseau mondial de bureaux et de partenaires, les programmes AVRR de lOIM favorisent le dialogue et la coopration lchelle internationale dans le domaine de la gestion des migrations entre les pays daccueil et de transit et les pays dorigine.

Objectifs


LOIM sefforce daider les migrants rintgrer durablement des pays aux contextes multiples. Elle sait que les facteurs influant sur le processus de rintgration et, terme, sur sa prennit sont les mmes que ceux ayant motiv la migration. Elle estime, de ce fait, que la rintgration des migrants rentrs au pays est considre comme durable lorsque ceux-ci ont atteint un niveau dautonomie financire, de stabilit sociale au sein de leur communaut et de bien-tre psychosocial suffisamment lev pour compenser les facteurs de (re)migration. Pour les migrants qui se rinsrent ainsi durablement dans leur pays, la migration nest plus une ncessit, mais un choix. Pour atteindre cet objectif, la rintgration des migrants doit tre envisage de manire globale, en agissant sur les facteurs susceptibles dinfluencer ce processus, de manire rpondre aux besoins de lindividu et des communauts locales de faon mutuellement bnfique et liminer les obstacles structurels sous-jacents. Par consquent, laide aux migrants et aux communauts dans lesquelles ces derniers retournent, de mme que lamlioration des conditions structurelles des pays dorigine sont essentielles pour garantir une rintgration durable.

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_establishedin1951:
Fonde en 1951, l'Organisation internationale pour les migrations (OIM) est la principale organisation intergouvernementale dans le domaine de la migration et travaille en troite collaboration avec les partenaires gouvernementaux, intergouvernementaux et nongouvernementaux.

Avec 166 tats membres, 8 autres tats ayant le statut d'observateur et des bureaux dans plus de 100 pays, lOIM se consacre la promotion de la migration humaine et ordonne pour le bnfice de tous. Elle le fait en fournissant des services et des conseils aux gouvernements et aux migrants.

L'OIM contribue assurer la gestion humaine et ordonne des migrations, promouvoir la coopration internationale sur les questions de migration, aider la recherche de solutions pratiques aux problmes de migration et fournir une assistance humanitaire aux migrants dans le besoin, notamment les personnes rfugies et dplaces.

La Constitution de lOIM reconnat quune relation existe entre la migration et les conditions conomiques, sociales et culturelles, ainsi que le droit de libre circulation.

LOIM intervient dans les quatre grands domaines de la gestion des migrations:

  • Migration et dveloppement
  • Faciliter la migration
  • Rglementer les migrations
  • Migration force

Les activits de lOIM recoupant ces quatre domaines comprennent la promotion du droit international de la migration, le dbat et les orientations politiques, la protection des droits des migrants, la sant des migrants et la dimension sexospcifique de la migration.

i18nStrings.iom_aboutIOM_browser:
Cre en 1951, lOIM est lorganisation intergouvernementale chef de file dans le domaine de la migration. Elle collabore troitement avec ses partenaires gouvernementaux, intergouvernementaux et non gouvernementaux.

Compose de 166Etats Membres et de huit Etats observateurs, lOIM possde des bureaux dans plus de cent pays. Elle est rsolue promouvoir des migrations ordonnes et respectueuses de la dignit humaine dans lintrt de tous. Pour ce faire, elle fournit des services et des conseils aux gouvernements et aux migrants.

LOIM semploie faire en sorte que les migrations soient gres de manire humaine et ordonne, promouvoir la coopration internationale sur les questions de migration, faciliter la recherche de solutions pratiques aux problmes migratoires et fournir une assistance humanitaire aux migrants dans le besoin, y compris aux rfugis et aux personnes dplaces lintrieur de leur pays.

La Constitution de lOIM reconnat le lien entre la migration et le dveloppement conomique, social et culturel, de mme que le droit la libert de circulation.

LOIM dploie son action dans les quatre grands domaines suivants:

  • Migration et dveloppement
  • Migration assiste
  • Migration rgule
  • Migration force

Un certain nombre de ses activits recoupent ces quatre domaines. Ce sont notamment la promotion du droit international de la migration, le dbat et les orientations politiques, la protection des droits des migrants, la sant dans le contexte migratoire et la dimension sexospcifique de la migration.
i18nStrings.iom_aboutIOM_text:
Fonde en 1951, l'Organisation internationale pour les migrations (OIM) est la principale organisation intergouvernementale dans le domaine de la migration et travaille en troite collaboration avec les partenaires gouvernementaux, intergouvernementaux et nongouvernementaux.

Avec 169 tats membres, 8 autres tats ayant le statut d'observateur et des bureaux dans plus de 100 pays, lOIM est ddie la promotion de la migration humaine et ordonne pour le bnfice de tous. Elle le fait en fournissant des services et des conseils aux gouvernements et aux migrants.

L'OIM contribue assurer la gestion humaine et ordonne des migrations, promouvoir la coopration internationale sur les questions de migration, aider la recherche de solutions pratiques aux problmes de migration et fournir une assistance humanitaire aux migrants dans le besoin, notamment les personnes rfugies et dplaces.

La Constitution de lOIM reconnat quune relation existe entre la migration et les conditions conomiques, sociales et culturelles, ainsi que le droit de libre circulation.

LOIM intervient dans les quatre grands domaines de la gestion des migrations:

Migration et dveloppement
Faciliter la migration
Rglementer les migrations
Migration force

Les activits de lOIM recoupant ces quatre domaines comprennent la promotion du droit international de la migration, le dbat et les orientations politiques, la protection des droits des migrants, la sant des migrants et la dimension sexospcifique de la migration.

i18nStrings.iom_travelInformationIntro: Le service daide au voyage de lOIM facilite le dplacement des migrants et rduit le stress qui accompagne souvent un premier voyage  ltranger. Il fournit aux migrants des informations sur les transports ariens ainsi quune aide sur place  lachat de billets davion  prix rduit. Le programme Missions de lOIM propose aux migrants des billets davion aller spciaux  prix rduit  destination du Canada,  des tats-Unis dAmrique, de lEurope et de lAustralie. Lobjectif est de faciliter le voyage des immigrants titulaires dun visa et des tudiants ou travailleurs temporaires titulaires dun visa de long sjour dune dure de validit suprieure  un an.

i18nStrings.i18n_about_vr:
Il programma di Rimpatrio volontario assistito e di reinserimento (AVRR) costituisce una parte essenziale di un approccio omnicomprensivo alla gestione della migrazione, volto a eseguire una procedura di rimpatrio e di reinserimento ordinata e rispettosa della dignit umana per migranti che non possono o non vogliono rimanere nei paesi ospiti e desiderano ritornare volontariamente al proprio paese d'origine.

La proficua attuazione dei programmi AVRR richiede la cooperazione e il coinvolgimento di un ampio ventaglio di partecipanti, inclusi i migranti, la societ civile e i governi tanto presso i paesi ospiti che presso quelli d'origine. I partenariati creati dall'OIM, nonch l'ampia gamma di portatori d'interesse nazionali e internazionali, sono indispensabili per l'attuazione efficace delle AVRR, dalle fasi antecedenti al ritorno sino allo stadio di reinserimento.

Beneficiari


Per i migranti che necessitano di tornare al paese d'origine ma non possiedono i mezzi per farlo, i programmi AVRR dell'OIM costituiscono spesso nell'immediato l'unica soluzione alle loro vicissitudini. I beneficiari dell'assistenza OIM includono:
Individui la cui domanda d'asilo stata respinta o ritirata
Migranti in difficolt
Vittime della tratta di esseri umani e
Altri gruppi vulnerabili, ivi inclusi migranti minorenni non accompagnati, o coloro che necessitano di attenzioni mediche

Visione


In qualit di attivit cardine dell'OIM, i programmi AVRR forniscono assistenza vitale a migliaia di migranti ogni anno. Forti di una lunga esperienza e di una rete globale di uffici e partner, i programmi AVRR dell'OIM promuovono il dialogo internazionale e la cooperazione su questioni relative alla gestione migratoria nei paesi ospiti e di transito cos come in quelli di origine.

Gli obiettivi


perseguiti dall'OIM consistono nel reinserimento sostenibile dei migranti che fanno ritorno a contesti quanto pi diversi, riconoscendo che i fattori che influenzano il processo di reinserimento e la relativa sostenibilit non sono dissimili dalle cause che hanno spinto a intraprendere il processo di migrazione in primo luogo. L'OIM pertanto ritiene che il reinserimento possa essere considerato sostenibile laddove i rimpatriandi abbiano raggiunto livelli di autosufficienza economica, stabilit sociale all'interno delle proprie comunit, nonch benessere psicosociale che permetta loro di affrontare i fattori migratori e di ritorno pi critici. Una volta compiuto un reinserimento sostenbile, i rimpatriandi sono in grado di operare ulteriori decisioni pertinenti alla propria migrazione su base volontaria, e non pi costretti da necessit. Per conseguire tale obiettivo, necessario affrontare il reinserimento migratorio con un approccio olistico, che tenga conto dei fattori che possono influire sul tale processo affrontadoli in maniera mutualmente benefica tanto ai bisogni individuali dei rimpatriandi che alle comunit di ritorno, contemplando altres i fattori strutturali contingenti. L'assistenza ai migranti, alle comunit di rimpatrio, e il contesto ambientale dei paesi d'origine costituiscono pertanto un elemento essenziale per garantire la sostenibilit del processo di reinserimento.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_eligible: Se ha diritto ad assistenza in natura per il reinserimento, ricever una lettera (Termini di riferimento) prima della partenza recante l'importo esatto. Con tale lettera, contatti l'OIM del Suo paese d'origine entro tre mesi dall'arrivo per avviare la registrazione all'attivit desiderata. L'OIM La guider attraverso il processo e controller i Suoi progressi fino a circa un anno dopo il vostro ritorno.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_establishedin1951:
Fondata nel 1951, l'OIM la principale organizzazione intergovernativa nell'ambito della migrazione e lavora a stretto contatto con partner governativi, intergovernativi e non governativi.

Con 166 Stati membri, 8 Stati osservatori e uffici in oltre 100 paesi, l'OIM si impegna a favore di una migrazione rispettosa della dignit umana e ordinata che sia di beneficio a tutti. Tale missione ottemperata fornendo servizi e consulenza ai governi e ai migranti.

L'OIM si adopera per garantire una gestione della migrazione ordinata e rispettosa della dignit umana, per promuovere la cooperazione internazionale in materia di migrazione, per contribuire alla ricerca di soluzioni pratiche ai problemi della migrazione e per fornire assistenza umanitaria ai migranti bisognosi, compresi i rifugiati e gli sfollati interni.

La Costituzione dell'OIM riconosce il legame tra la migrazione e lo sviluppo economico, sociale e culturale, nonch il diritto alla libera circolazione.

L'OIM opera nei quattro grandi settori della gestione della migrazione:

  • Migrazione e sviluppo
  • Agevolazione della migrazione
  • Regolamentazione della migrazione
  • Migrazione forzata

Le attivit dell'OIM in questi settori comprendono la promozione del diritto internazionale in materia di migrazione, il dibattito politico e l'orientamento, la protezione dei diritti dei migranti, lo stato di salute dei migranti e la dimensione di genere della migrazione.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iom's: Il Programma OIM di rimpatrio volontario asstistito & il reinserimento (AVRR)  attualmente disponibile nei seguenti paesi:
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassist:
L'OIM pu assisterLa nell'ottenere i documenti di viaggio idonei qualora ne sia sprovvisto/a.

In caso di problemi medici, possiamo altres programmare una visita medica. L'OIM pu inoltre assisterLa fornendo farmaci e sostegno prima, durante e dopo il viaggio
.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_iomcanassistdocuments: L'OIM pu assisterLa nell'ottenemento dei documenti di viaggio idonei, qualora ne sia sprovvisto/a, o aiutarLa a richiedere i documenti al governo. In caso di problemi medici, possiamo valutare le Sue esigenze in collaborazione con un medico indipendente. L'OIM pu anche assisterLa con cure e sostegno prima, durante e dopo il viaggio. Una volta concluso l'approntamento, e la candidatura approvata, l'OIM prenoter il biglietto per la Sua destinazione finale.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_netherlands: Sin dal 1991 l'OIM Paesi Bassi ha aiutato pi di 60.000 persone a tornare al proprio paese d'origine. Siamo qui per assicurarci che Lei sia a conoscenza di tutte le opzioni a Sua disposizione. Le spiegheremo in dettaglio come funziona il nostro servizio.

Il personale dell'OIM prenoter il Suo biglietto, La incontrer in aeroporto e La assister con il check-in e le formalit doganali. Una volta atterrato/a, l'OIM La incontrer all'arrivo e pu anche organizzare il trasferimento dall'aeroporto alla destinazione finale

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_since:
Depuis le lancement du programme AVRR, de nombreuses personnes ont pu retourner dans leur pays grce nos services. Nous sommes ici pour vous expliquer en dtail les diffrentes solutions qui soffrent vous et le fonctionnement de notre service.

Une fois en possession des informations ncessaires, vous pouvez prendre le temps de rflchir la suite de votre dmarche. Vous pouvez changer davis nimporte quelle tape de la procdure. Nous ne communiquerons vos informations personnelles aucun tiers.

Sin dal 1979, l'OIM, l'Agenzia delle Nazioni Unite per le Migrazioni, ha aiutato oltre un milione e mezzo di persone a ritornare al proprio paese d'origine, attraverso i suoi programmi di rimpatrio volontario assistito e di reinserimento, comunemente noti come AVRR. Siamo qui per assicurarci che Lei sia a conoscenza di tutte le opzioni a Sua disposizione e Le spiegheremo esattamente come funziona il nostro servizio

Una volta che avr tutte le informazioni necessarie, potr dedicare un po' di tempo per pensare al Suo prossimo passo. Pu cambiare idea in qualsiasi fase del processo. L'intero processo avviene su base confidenziale

i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_understand:
Comprendiamo che tornare al proprio paese d'origine sia una decisione importante.

Se desidera tornare o discutere le opzioni in modo riservato, l'OIM pu fornire assistenza su misura per le Sue esigenze e circostanze.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_upon:
Una volta presa la decisione di tornare al paese d'origine, insieme possiamo concepire un piano sulla base della Sua data desiderata di partenza

Il personale dell'OIM prenoter il Suo biglietto, La incontrer in aeroporto e La assister con il check-in e le formalit doganali. Una volta atterrato/a, l'OIM La incontrer all'arrivo e pu anche organizzare il trasferimento dall'aeroporto alla destinazione finale
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_weunderstand: Comprendiamo che tornare nel proprio paese possa essere una decisione difficile. Se si desidera ritornare o discutere le proprie opzioni in modo riservato, possibile fissare un appuntamento per una consulenza oraria presso l'ufficio OIM pi vicino. L'OIM presente presso le sedi del COA e in molte altre localit del paese.
i18nStrings.i18n_avrr_whenyouarrive:
Una volta arrivato/a all'aeroporto, necessario recarsi al Banco OIM dove ricever il biglietto. Un membro del personale dell'OIM La assister durante le formalit di check-in e di uscita e, se necessario, durante il transito e all'arrivo. Se ha diritto a una sovvenzione in contanti, ricever il dovuto importo dopo il check-in.
.

i18nStrings.i18n_common_establishedin1951:
Fondata nel 1951, l'OIM la principale organizzazione intergovernativa nell'ambito della migrazione e lavora a stretto contatto con partner governativi, intergovernativi e non governativi.

Con 166 Stati membri, 8 Stati osservatori e uffici in oltre 100 paesi, l'OIM si impegna a favore di una migrazione rispettosa della dignit umana e ordinata che sia di beneficio per tutti. Tale missione ottemperata fornendo servizi e consulenza ai governi e ai migranti.

L'OIM si adopera per garantire una gestione della migrazione ordinata e rispettosa della dignit umana, per promuovere la cooperazione internazionale in materia di migrazione, per contribuire alla ricerca di soluzioni pratiche ai problemi della migrazione e per fornire assistenza umanitaria ai migranti bisognosi, compresi i rifugiati e gli sfollati interni.

La Costituzione dell'OIM riconosce il legame tra la migrazione e lo sviluppo economico, sociale e culturale, nonch il diritto alla libera circolazione.

L'OIM opera nei quattro grandi settori della gestione della migrazione:

Migrazione e sviluppo
Agevolazione della migrazione
Regolamentazione della migrazione
Migrazione forzata

Le attivit dell'OIM in questi settori comprendono la promozione del diritto internazionale in materia di migrazione, il dibattito politico e l'orientamento, la protezione dei diritti dei migranti, lo stato di salute dei migranti e la dimensione di genere della migrazione.

i18nStrings.i18n_ecointro_iom's:
L'ufficio dell'OIM per il codice etico e di condotta (ECO) riceve, gestisce e tiene traccia delle segnalazioni riguardanti presunti comportamenti illeciti e immorali in conformit con gli standard di condotta dell'OIM e le relative politiche, incluse frodi, molestie, abusi di autorit, discriminazioni e conflitti di interesse.

L'intero personale dell'OIM ha l'obbligo di segnalare comportamenti illeciti e immorali all'ECO all'indirizzo eco@iom.int. Le terze parti sono altres invitate a presentare direttamente all'ECO (eco@iom.int) qualsiasi rapporto o reclamo relativo a qualsivoglia violazione delle norme di condotta dell'OIM da parte di un membro del personale dell'OIM.
